  <h1>
   The Physics World
  </h1>
  Before any physical reactions can occur in
  <span>
   GameMaker
  </span>
  you must first define the physics world in which they are going to happen. If you do not do this,
  <span>
   GameMaker
  </span>
  will default to the basic collision functions, and all other physics related code or settings will be ignored. You can set up the physics world from the
  <a href="../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Room_Properties/Room_Properties.htm">
   Room Editor
  </a>
  , but you can also set the same properties using code with the following functions:
  <ul>
   <li>
    <a href="physics_world_create.htm">
     physics_world_create
    </a>
   </li>
   <li>
    <a href="physics_world_gravity.htm">
     physics_world_gravity
    </a>
   </li>
   <li>
    <a href="physics_world_update_iterations.htm">
     physics_world_update_iterations
    </a>
   </li>
   <li>
    <a href="physics_world_update_speed.htm">
     physics_world_update_speed
    </a>
   </li>
   <li>
    <a href="physics_world_draw_debug.htm">
     physics_world_draw_debug
    </a>
   </li>
   <li>
    <a href="physics_draw_debug.htm">
     physics_draw_debug
    </a>
   </li>
   <li>
    <a href="physics_pause_enable.htm">
     physics_pause_enable
    </a>
   </li>
  </ul>
